useful shit with pacman
          # pacman -Rns (software + dependecies) 
          $ pacman -Qdt (unneeded dependencies) 
          $ pacman -Ss (search)
          $/#  pacman -Fy /usr/bin/{software} (tells the package from the bin) (edited)
          $ pacman -Qn (all packages installed from main repo)
          $ pacman -Qm (all packages installed from the AUR)
          $ sudo pacman -Qi (tells you the version)
